170 g Fusilli
250 g Mild Italian Sausage, uncased
56 g Yellow Onion, chopped
1 unit(s) Beef Broth Concentrate
1 tbsp Garlic Puree
1 unit(s) Cream Cheese
227 g Mushrooms
1 tbsp Soy Sauce
56 g Green Peas
1 tbsp Cream Sauce Spice Blend
½ tbsp Oil*
¼ tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
¼ cup Milk*

Add fusilli to the boiling water. Cook uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender, 9-11 min.
Reserve 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) pasta water, then drain and return fusilli to the same pot, off heat.

Thinly slice mushrooms.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then sausage and soy sauce. Cook, breaking up sausage into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.** Season with salt and pepper.
Using a slotted spoon, transfer the sausage to a bowl.

Add mushrooms, peas, onions and garlic to the same pan. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, 3-4 min. Season with salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to medium.
Return sausage to the pan. Stir to combine.
Sprinkle over Cream Sauce Spice Blend. Cook, stirring often, until veggies and sausage are coated, 1 min.

Add cream cheese, broth concentrate, garlic, 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) milk and reserved pasta water. Cook, stirring often, until slightly thickened, 2-3 min. Season with salt and pepper.

Add sausage mixture to the pot with noodles. Stir to combine.
Divide creamy sausage fusili between bowls.

If you've opted to get sausage, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the beef.